# Clean sync / refresh / digest UX

## Manual refresh — one place only

- **Only** the header `…` (More) menu **Refresh** control may trigger a user-initiated full refresh (prices, media feeds, and cloud sync when configured).
- Do **not** add page-level **Sync now**, **Sync prices**, **Cloud Sync →**, or **Refresh** buttons/thumbs/header actions anywhere else in the product chrome.
- Do **not** restore long-press force-sync on the sync status chip or bottom-nav items.
- Auto-refresh when quotes are stale (and brief non-interactive “Refreshing data” status) is encouraged.
- **Settings → Sync** may keep setup controls (Remote URL, passphrase, Automatic sync, and a Sync now for first-device setup). That is configuration, not Overview chrome.

## Digest

- **Weekly digest** (Preview/Share) lives in the **burger / Sidebar** only — not in the Today/Overview hero, Markets aside, or Compare header.
- Opening digest from the sidebar may navigate to `/?digest=1` or dispatch `mydsp-open-weekly-digest`.

## Sync status chip

- The header chip is **status + deep-link to Settings → Sync** (e.g. Unlock sync). It must not offer another manual sync gesture.

## Pull-to-refresh

- PTR may remain as a gesture on approved routes; it must not add visible Sync/Refresh CTAs.
